and the eugenic implications of preimplantation genetic diagnosis. Celeste E. Orr investigates how intersex and interphobia intersect with disability and ableism to propose a new approach to intersex studies and activism. The integration of feminist disability studies with intersex studies provides tools to break down the traditional sex dyad and the entrenched cultural mandate against intersex traits. This necessary work offers a radical new understanding of intersex-with-disability, pushing analyses of intersex histories, experience, and embodiment further than feminist or queer theory can do alone.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDiscrimination against intersex people2DLC. 0aDiscrimination against intersex people. 0aDiscrimination against people with disabilities2DLC. 0aDiscrimination against people with disabilities. 0aIntersex people2DLC. 0aIntersex peoplexHealth and hygiene2DLC. 0aIntersex peoplexHealth and hygiene. 0aIntersex peoplexIdentity2DLC. 0aIntersex peoplexIdentity. 0aIntersex peoplexMedical care2DLC. 0aIntersex peoplexMedical care. 0aIntersex peoplexPsychology2DLC. 0aIntersex peoplexPsychology. 0aIntersex peoplexSocial conditions2DLC. 0aIntersex peoplexSocial conditions. 0aIntersex people. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311141763940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486854940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774868549423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774868549/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-P